üéØ Basic Streamlit Interview Questions (Simple Words)
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Streamlit?

A Python framework used to build web apps for data science and ML easily.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Why do we use Streamlit?

Because it lets you make dashboards and apps fast without HTML/JS.

3Ô∏è‚É£ How to run a Streamlit app?

By using:

streamlit run app.py

4Ô∏è‚É£ How to display text in Streamlit?

Using:

st.write("Hello")
st.text("Hello")
st.title("My App")

5Ô∏è‚É£ How to show a dataframe?
st.dataframe(df)

6Ô∏è‚É£ How to add a button?
if st.button("Click me"):
    st.write("Button clicked")

7Ô∏è‚É£ How to upload a file?
file = st.file_uploader("Upload CSV", type=["csv"])

8Ô∏è‚É£ How to create input fields?
name = st.text_input("Enter name")
age = st.number_input("Enter age")

9Ô∏è‚É£ How to show charts?
st.line_chart(df)
st.bar_chart(df)

üîü Where to store data temporarily?

Use session_state:

st.session_state["key"] = value

üéØ Intermediate Streamlit Questions (Simple Words)
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is Session State?

A place where Streamlit stores values so they don‚Äôt reset on rerun.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Why does Streamlit rerun the script on every interaction?

That's how Streamlit is designed ‚Äî it re-executes the script when user clicks or updates any widget.

3Ô∏è‚É£ How to avoid rerunning heavy code again and again?

Use caching:

@st.cache_data
def load_data():
    ...

4Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between cache_data and cache_resource?

cache_data ‚Üí stores data output

cache_resource ‚Üí stores objects like models, DB connections

5Ô∏è‚É£ How to create multiple pages?

By adding files in pages/ folder.

6Ô∏è‚É£ How to hide the Streamlit menu and footer?
st.markdown("""
<style>
#MainMenu {visibility: hidden;}
footer {visibility: hidden;}
</style>
""", unsafe_allow_html=True)

7Ô∏è‚É£ How to change layout to wide?
st.set_page_config(layout="wide")

8Ô∏è‚É£ Can Streamlit call APIs?

Yes:

import requests
response = requests.get("https://api...")

9Ô∏è‚É£ How to run ML models in Streamlit?

Load the model and run prediction when user clicks a button.

üîü How to create tabs or columns?
tab1, tab2 = st.tabs(["Tab 1", "Tab 2"])
col1, col2 = st.columns(2)

üéØ Advanced Streamlit Interview Questions (Simple Words)
1Ô∏è‚É£ How to deploy Streamlit?

Streamlit Cloud

Render

Azure

AWS

Docker

2Ô∏è‚É£ What is Streamlit Cloud?

Free hosting service for Streamlit apps.

3Ô∏è‚É£ How does Streamlit handle state?

Internally, it stores widget changes in session_state.

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between Streamlit and Flask?
Streamlit	Flask
Used for dashboards & ML apps	Used to build any backend
No HTML needed	HTML/JS needed
Faster to build	More flexible
5Ô∏è‚É£ How to create custom components?

Using Streamlit Components API (React + JS + Python).

6Ô∏è‚É£ How to connect Streamlit with a database?

Using Python libraries (sqlite3, psycopg2, SQLAlchemy).

7Ô∏è‚É£ Does Streamlit support real-time updates?

Yes, using st.experimental_rerun() or WebSocket components.

8Ô∏è‚É£ What is st.sidebar?

A vertical panel for filters, inputs, and navigation.

9Ô∏è‚É£ How to stop Streamlit execution?
st.stop()

üîü How to show progress or loading spinner?
with st.spinner("Loading..."):
    time.sleep(3)
